        <updateDate>2022-11-08T15:13:23Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Preserving the Readiness of our Armed Forces Act of 2022</strong></p> <p>This bill provides that a member of the National Guard (or another reserve component) must maintain access to pay and benefits while a request for a religious or health accommodation is pending. Additionally, a member of an active or reserve component of the Armed Forces may not be involuntarily separated from the Armed Forces based solely on COVID-19 vaccination status until specified recruiting goals are achieved.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
